scenario:
No violation in this code fragment: it invokes an external callback function pointer cb passed into lfs_fs_traverse_ / lfs_ctz_traverse_. The enclosing functions do not call themselves directly. A rule-17.2 violation would only occur if the caller supplied a callback that calls back into the same traversal function (creating indirect recursion). For example, if the user provided

static int cb(void *data, lfs_block_t block) { return lfs_fs_traverse_(lfs, cb, data, false); }

then lfs_fs_traverse_ -> cb -> lfs_fs_traverse_ would create indirect recursion and violate Rule 17.2.
